commit.message:
Minor simplifications.

Removes a few extraneous parentheses that aren't needed due to operator
precedence.

Fix use of "dx" in examples.

Compared to WebKit, this seems to be handled differently by current
versions of Firefox and Opera, perhaps due to an ambiguity in the spec.:

  http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-svg/2011Dec/0009.html

d3.format: support align and non-decimal formats.

This also fixes a minor discrepancy with Python's implementation:
format("013,d")(-42000000) now returns "-0,042,000,000" instead of
"-042,000,000".

Rename d3_path_circle for consistency.

I guess this may end up in d3.svg at some point, but consistency is
good!

Simplify d3.geo.bounds implementation.

Also, add rudimentary test.

Add d3.geo.path.bounds.

This computes the bounding box for a given GeoJSON object using the
current projection.

d3.format: Always apply locale decimal point.

It should be applied even when no grouping is used. Thanks, @mbostock!
d3.format: fix decimal points for null grouping.

d3.format: support locales.

Note: the previous commit broke some tests relating to locale date
parsing, due to expecting "%m/%d/%y". On my system, the "en_US" locale
uses "%m/%d/%Y" by default. I've updated the tests to use %Y.

Update to UglifyJS v1.3.3.

Also, update node-canvas to v0.13.0 for better compatibility with
Node.js v0.8.x.
Improve handling of intermediate locale files.

Automate d3.time.format locale generation.

This avoids having to include a large number of locales in the D3
repository, and also reduces the potential for typos when transcribing
locale mappings.

Merge pull request #761 from jasondavies/time-en_GB

Add en_GB locale for d3.time.format.

Add d3.lab and d3.hcl.

Includes d3.interpolateLab and d3.interpolateHcl.

Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/map' into 2.10.0

Conflicts:
	src/core/transition-attr.js
	src/core/transition-style.js

Expose d3.tween. Fixes #747.

This is a little bit more verbose, but it avoids additional optional arguments
on transition.{attr,style}.

Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/custom-line-interpolation' into 2.10.0

Conflicts:
	src/svg/line.js

Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/transition-interpolate' into 2.10.0

Conflicts:
	src/core/interpolate.js

Allow static localization of d3.time.format.

You can now build a locale-specific version of d3.time.format. For example,

  LANG=fr_FR make

will pull strings from the time/format-fr_FR.js file, rather than en_US.
Remove support for functions that return maps.

Revert piecewise interpolation for transforms.

Rather than adopting CSS’s elaborate rules for detecting when the start and end
transform are the same type as using piecewise (i.e., string-based)
interpolation, we always use the consolidated transform transition. If you want
to use string-based interpolation, simply specify d3.interpolateString as the
interpolator. Fixes #746.

Custom interpolators for transition.{attr, style}.

Fixes #747.

Use hyphen instead of unicode minus for negatives.

Although the unicode minus is typographically correct, using the standard hyphen
is more conventional (and is compatible with standard parsing).

Fix rotate transforms with non-zero origin.

Previously, only the angle was being interpolated. Unfortunately, it
looks like the origin information is lost when converted to a matrix.
For example, "rotate(0 100 100)" is the identity matrix [1 0 0 1 0 0].
Interpolating the matrix decomposition seems better than dropping the
origin altogether.

Fix nice implementation for time scales.

The previous implementation didn't handle polylinear domains correctly.
